{#
  SPT (Subspace Product Tucker) driver.

  Verified against:
    test/test_spt.jl
    test/test_openshell.jl
    test/test_variance.jl
    examples/bimetallics/benchmark_variance_m100.jl
    examples/tetracene_dimer/spt_direct.jl

  Workflow
  --------
  1. Build spin-adapted eigenbasis with compute_cluster_eigenbasis_spin.
  2. Seed an SPTstate directly, with one of two P-space modes:
       "open_shell" — automatic Cr2-style low-spin p_spaces:
                      every open-shell cluster gets all spin distributions
                      between (high,low) and (low,high), closed-shell clusters
                      keep only the reference sector. Then fill_p_space!(na, nb).
       "ct"         — SPT/direct CT-style seed:
                      reference SPTstate + single excitons + double excitons
                      + spin-flip states.
  3. CI solve the SPT P-space.
  4. subspace_product_tucker for variational SPT.
  5. Optional post-SPT analysis: PT2 correction or variance-like estimate.

  Old FermiCG name: block_sparse_tucker → TPSChem.subspace_product_tucker

  post_analysis options:
    "none"      — just save and exit
    "pt2"       — compute_pt2_energy_blockwise on v_var (fast SPT-PT2)
    "variance"  — compute_spt_sigma_norm_blockwise_alternative, then sigma2 - E^2
#}
